The data were collected and made freely available by the International Argo Program (http://www.argo.ucsd.edu, http://argo.jcommops.org). The Argo Program is part of the Global Ocean Observing System [21]. The Argo floats operate in a network of 2000–3000 floats, recording data such as temperature and salinity as a function of pressure. AVISO altimetry on the other hand was employed to calculate absolute dynamic depth. The temporal resolution of the data is monthly and spans from January 2010 to December 2012. The spatial resolution of the dataset is 1∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
