In estimations where profits are generated after a certain time lapse after investments, the net present value (NPV) estimations are considered. Banerjee et al. [54] proposed the following relationship to determine the cost of electricity from the NPV concept pertaining to the generation cost alone and excluding the insurance cost, local taxes, profit margin among others.24Costofelectricityproduction(perkWh)=Cc+∑0t[0.01x.Cc/(1+r)t]∑0t[E/(1+r)t]\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
