				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} \mathrm{Cost~of~electricity~production}~(\mathrm{per}~\mathrm{kWh})=\frac{\left\{ \mathrm{Cc}+\sum _{0}^{t}[0.01x.\mathrm{Cc}/(1+r)t]\right\} }{\left\{ \sum _{0}^{t}[E/(1+r)t]\right\} } \end{aligned}$$\end{document}where Cc is the capital cost, E is the annual energy production, t is the life period, r represents the discount rate considered, while the operational cost is x percent of the capital cost Cc.

